        </mml:math>
      </disp-formula>
    </p>
    <p>where lwindow is the size of the left window (300 bp).</p>
    <p>TopHat-Fusion outputs alignments of singleton reads and paired-end reads mapped across fusion points in SAM format [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B28">28</xref>], enabling further downstream analyses [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B29">29</xref>], such as transcript assembly and differential gene expression. The parameters in the filtering steps can be changed as needed for a particular data set.</p>
  </sec>
  <sec>
    <title>Abbreviations</title>
    <p>bp: base pair; DASPER: difference between observed and expected SPER; IUM: initially unmapped; RESPER: ratio of observed SPER to the average of all SPERs; SAM: Sequence Alignment/Map; SPER: supportive paired-end reads; UHR: universal human reference.</p>
  </sec>
  <sec>
    <title>Authors' contributions</title>
    <p>DK developed the TopHat-Fusion algorithms, performed the analysis and discussed the results, implemented TopHat-Fusion and wrote the manuscript. SLS developed the TopHat-Fusion algorithms, performed the analysis and discussed the results, and wrote the manuscript. All authors have read and approved the manuscript for publication.</p>
